\section*{Cellular Barriers Phagocytosis}
$\square$ carried out by 2 types of leukocytes in the blood:
- neutrophils, a type of granulocyte (60-70\%)
- monocytes, a type of agranulocyte (3-8\%)
$\square$ phagocytes in the body can be divided into 2 types:
- microphages (e.g., neutrophils) - phagocytic against bacteria in the early phases of infection
- macrophages - fixed in tissues (reticuloendothelial system); active against microbes, dead and dying microphages, dead tissue
